question: I was admitted Monday at my drs appt because of preeclampsia and was to be induced tonight/tomorrow at 3a.m... Well Brantley had other plans I was woken up at 5a.m. for vitals and blood work for my magnesium level well I tried going back to sleep after nurse was done but I had little pains in my back going into the front... So I made my nurse aware of this about 5:30-6a.m. she told me time them n shed b back.. I had 7 in a half hr they then put me on monitors and checked me I was at a 3 Hr later checked I was at 3+ and 80% effaced. Got me to the L&D suite checked again half hr later n was at 5-6 another hr was at a 7 still no epidural and I'm like freaking out cuz of the back labor ready to rip faces off. Finally got the epidural at about 10:30 n was good for a while. Water was broke at 1:40 and after that no progression till bout 5p.m was at a 9 then checked again n i was at a 10 but waited a Lil bit for him to come down more in birth canal finally at 7:21 I started pushing and he arrived at 7:28p.m. 6lb 11oz. 18⅜ inches long. He's so precious and my everything along with his big brother and their dad.
title: birth story of Brantley
